ADAT Lightpipe Digital Audio Signal Dumps
=========================================

ADAT (Alesis Digital Audio Tape) Lightpipe is a digital audio protocol
that transmits 8 channels of 24-bit audio over optical fiber.

Protocol Details:
-----------------
- 8 channels of digital audio
- 24-bit resolution per channel
- Sample rates: 44.1, 48, 88.2, 96 kHz
- Optical transmission (TOSLINK)
- NRZI encoding
- Synchronization patterns

Files:
------
- adat_48khz_8ch.sr: 8-channel audio at 48 kHz
- adat_sync_pattern.sr: Synchronization frame
- adat_user_bits.sr: User data transmission

Frame Structure:
----------------
- 256 bits per frame
- 24 bits per channel Ã— 8 channels = 192 bits
- 4 user bits
- 4 sync bits
- NRZI encoded optical signal
